other_tests.findings: Confirmed the absence of the uterus and cervix. Right ovary was not visualized; clusters of simple cysts in the adnexal region on both sides.
Borderline low bone mass in the spine (T score, −1.10), normal bone mass in the vertebral bodies (T score, −0.20), and normal bone mass in the femoral neck (T score, −0.90).

No discernible uterus or cervix. Bilateral thin, linear, hyperintense tubelike structures along the course of the round ligaments, likely representing isthmic and interstitial segments of the fallopian tubes or lymphatic vessels.
Testes had multiple cystic structures and hamartomas composed of immature Sertoli cells. No gonadal masses identified.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Post-surgery, the patient began estrogen-containing hormone-replacement therapy.
